Some things CANNOT be done in code and must be done directly in the Base44 web editor.
When you encounter any of the following, STOP and tell the user exactly what to do in Base44 instead of trying to code a workaround:

- Adding/removing/renaming entity fields → "Go to Base44 → Entities → [EntityName] → edit the schema"
- Changing user roles or inviting users → "Go to Base44 → Users → Invite or edit role"
- Setting environment variables/secrets → "Go to Base44 → Settings → Environment Variables"
- Enabling/disabling GitHub sync → "Go to Base44 → Settings → GitHub Sync"
- Deploying the app → "Go to Base44 → Publish"
- Configuring a custom domain → "Go to Base44 → Settings → Custom Domain"
- Creating or managing automations (scheduled/entity triggers) → "Go to Base44 → Automations"
- Managing backend function deployment → "Go to Base44 → Code → Functions"
- Viewing production logs → "Go to Base44 → Code → Functions → [function name] → Logs"
- Auth/login configuration → "This is managed by Base44 platform, not configurable in code"
- Test vs Production database switching → "Go to Base44 → toggle Test/Prod in the top bar"

Format your response as: "⚠️ This requires a Base44 platform action: [exact steps]"
Do NOT attempt to replicate platform functionality in application code.
